DataElement.preferredName: Cytogenetics Nucleophosmin Anaplastic Lymphoma Kinase Evaluation Review Outcome
DataElement.preferredDefinition: the pathology review result related to the conventional cytogenetics of NPM-ALK t(2;5)(p23;q35). The 2;5 chromosomal translocation is frequently associated with anaplastic large cell lymphomas (ALCLs). The translocation creates a fusion gene consisting of the ALK (anaplastic lymphoma kinase) gene and the nucleophosmin (NPM) gene.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Cytogenetics is the study of chromosomes and the related disease states caused by numerical and structural chromosome abnormalities.

Concepts.definition: The branch of biology that studies the cellular aspects of heredity, especially the chromosomes. Includes the study of disease states caused by numerical and structural chromosome abnormalities.

Property.preferredDefinition: A human nuclear matrix protein with demonstrated immunohistochemical staining differences between benign and malignant prostate tissue.:The 2;5 chromosomal translocation is frequently associated with anaplastic large cell lymphomas (ALCLs). The translocation creates a fusion gene consisting of the ALK (anaplastic lymphoma kinase) gene and the nucleophosmin (NPM) gene: the 3' half of ALK, derived from chromosome 2, is fused to the 5' portion of NPM from chromosome 5. A recent study shows that the product of the NPM-ALK fusion gene is oncogenic. The deduced amino acid sequences reveal that ALK is a novel receptor protein-tyrosine kinase having a putative transmembrane domain and an extracellular domain. These sequences are absent in the product of the transforming NPM-ALK gene.:Systematic, objective appraisal of the significance, effectiveness, and impact of activities or condition according to specified objectives and criteria.

Concepts.definition: Nucleophosmin (294 aa, ~33 kDa) is encoded by the human NPM1 gene. This protein is involved in ribosomal function.
ALK tyrosine kinase receptor (1620 aa, ~176 kDa) is encoded by the human ALK gene. This protein is involved in ligand binding, tyrosine phosphorylation and signal transduction.
